  <div class="vt-datebar">
  <img src="./styles/absolution/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" />Posted: Fri Nov 12, 2010 12:40 pm 
  </div><!-- /vt-datebar --> 
            
       <div class="vt-postcontent">
       Hi Guys,<br /><br />I've just received a Stora and spent a few hours last night messing around trying to get various things installed/setup etc. I've got to the stage where I need to wipe the box and start from fresh (tried to too do many conflicting things and i've created a big mess).<br /><br />But I can see the above happening on a regular basis whilst I figure out what I'm doing/how to do it (even though I'm pretty much just copying/pasting from the wiki!).<br /><br />So... I decided that to make my life easier I would create a shell script that I could run (after I'd re-rooted the box) which would get me back to a reasonable state each time.<br /><br />** WIP v0.01 available on pastebin: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://pastebin.com/AVvC1B2j">http://pastebin.com/AVvC1B2j</a><!-- m --> **<br />** WIP v0.02 available on paste2: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://paste2.org/p/1091678">http://paste2.org/p/1091678</a><!-- m --> **<br />** WIP v0.03 available on pastebin: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://pastebin.com/QDjSFtTT">http://pastebin.com/QDjSFtTT</a><!-- m --> **<br /><br /><span style="text-decoration: underline">Screenshots:</span><br /><br /><img src="http://www.streetster.co.uk/img/stora_v3-1.png" alt="Image" /><br /><br /><img src="http://www.streetster.co.uk/img/stora_v3-2.png" alt="Image" /><br /><br /><span style="text-decoration: underline">Wiki:</span><br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.openstora.com/wiki/index.php?title=All-In-One_Installer_Script">http://www.openstora.com/wiki/index.php ... ler_Script</a><!-- m --><br /><br /><span style="text-decoration: underline">Changelog:</span><br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: <a href="#" onclick="selectCode(this); return false;">Select all</a></dt><dd><code>0.01 - Initial Release<br />0.02 - Menu Changed, few typo fixes<br />0.03 - Added Transmission bittorrent client</code></dd></dl><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Prerequisites:</span><br /><span style="font-size: 100%; line-height: 116%;"> - Netgear Stora <br /> - Root Access to Stora<br /> - Internet Access from Stora<br /> - 1 Harddrive (or 2 in RAID1 configuration)</span><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Recommended:</span><br /><span style="font-size: 100%; line-height: 116%;"> - Latest firmware update (allowing factory reset)</span><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Disclaimer:</span><br /><span style="font-size: 100%; line-height: 116%;">Whilst I have tested this script on my stora and it works for me, I make no guarantees that it will work for you. So <span style="font-weight: bold">use it at your own risk</span>. Please understand that if you do something stupid like setting your house on fire, divorce your wife, or brick your stora after using my script, don't come crying to me...</span><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Extra:</span><br /><span style="font-size: 100%; line-height: 116%;">If you have any thoughts/suggestions/problems/flames please reply to this thread to keep everything in one place. My Stora is no longer running the stock Netgear firmware but I will do my best to accomodate updates and to resolve issues.</span><br /><br />Cheers<br />Mark
       </div> 
       
       
